Dialogue: 0,0:00:00.00,0:00:00.00,DCMain,,0000,0000,0000,,Detective Conan Episode 130 \N"The Blank Year (Part One)"
Dialogue: 0,0:00:00.00,0:00:00.00,DCMain,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,[OP]
Dialogue: 0,0:00:00.64,0:00:04.48,Location Signs,SIGN,0000,0000,0000,,{\fad(444,435)\blur1}Within the Metropolitan Area, Koneru City{\b0}
Dialogue: 0,0:00:01.29,0:00:04.27,DCMain,KOGORO,0000,0000,0000,,{\an8}Now then. I finished my investigative report.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:04.27,0:00:05.98,DCMain,KOGORO,0000,0000,0000,,Here in Koneru City...
Dialogue: 0,0:00:07.13,0:00:10.02,DCMain,KOGORO,0000,0000,0000,,Maybe I'll go for a drink this afternoon.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:18.61,0:00:20.94,DCMain,KOGORO,0000,0000,0000,,What happened? Are you all right?
Dialogue: 0,0:00:20.94,0:00:25.67,DCMain,ESAKA,0000,0000,0000,,While I was waiting for the light to \Nchange, someone suddenly pushed my back.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:26.01,0:00:27.92,DCMain,ESAKA,0000,0000,0000,,I was nearly hit by a car.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:29.22,0:00:30.80,DCMain,KOGORO,0000,0000,0000,,Did anyone see the culprit?
Dialogue: 0,0:00:33.52,0:00:35.43,DCMain,KOGORO,0000,0000,0000,,Can you think of any reason \Nsomeone would want to kill you?
Dialogue: 0,0:00:35.61,0:00:37.43,DCMain,KOGORO,0000,0000,0000,,Does anyone have a grudge against you?
Dialogue: 0,0:00:38.92,0:00:40.84,DCMain,ESAKA,0000,0000,0000,,I can't think of anything.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:44.35,0:00:50.06,DCMain,ESAKA,0000,0000,0000,,No, maybe I did something to \Nthem during my blank year.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:51.14,0:00:53.60,DCMain,KOGORO,0000,0000,0000,,Blank year?
Dialogue: 0,0:00:54.20,0:00:58.09,DCMain,ESAKA,0000,0000,0000,,Are you Mori Kogoro-san, the great detective?
Dialogue: 0,0:00:58.09,0:00:58.86,DCMain,KOGORO,0000,0000,0000,,Yes.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:58.86,0:01:01.12,DCMain,ESAKA,0000,0000,0000,,My name is Esaka Ritsuo.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:01.33,0:01:04.75,Character Names,SIGN,0000,0000,0000,,{\fad(398,436)\pos(237,296)}Esaka Ritsuo (28)\NMan with Memory Loss
Dialogue: 0,0:01:01.40,0:01:05.75,DCMain,ESAKA,0000,0000,0000,,{\an8}Please find the past that's \Nbeen erased from my memory.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:06.77,0:01:09.06,DCMain,KOGORO,0000,0000,0000,,Find the past?
Dialogue: 0,0:01:21.68,0:01:23.64,DCMain,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,Finally arriving after \Nswaying back and forth,
Dialogue: 0,0:01:23.64,0:01:25.38,DCMain,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,draw close to mysteries and \Nbegin deducing the truth!
Dialogue: 0,0:01:25.38,0:01:26.81,DCMain,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,A whole year lost!
Dialogue: 0,0:01:26.81,0:01:28.66,DCMain,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,With his life in danger, he \Nsearches for his memories!
Dialogue: 0,0:01:28.66,0:01:30.29,DCMain,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,Always determining the one truth
Dialogue: 0,0:01:30.29,0:01:32.08,DCMain,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,with the body of a child \Nand the mind of an adult,
Dialogue: 0,0:01:32.08,0:01:34.91,DCMain,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,his name is Detective Conan!
Dialogue: 0,0:03:06.95,0:03:12.96,DCEpTitle,EPTITLE,0000,0000,0000,,{\fad(403,1)\pos(323,64)}The Blank Year \N(Part One)
Dialogue: 0,0:03:07.41,0:03:10.51,DCMain,SIGN,0000,0000,0000,,"The Blank Year, Part One!"
Dialogue: 0,0:03:12.96,0:03:16.46,DCMain,SIGN,0000,0000,0000,,{\an8\b1\fnTimesNewRoman\bord2\shad0\c&HF2EEEA&\3c&H9D7645&\fs24}Mori Detective Agency
Dialogue: 0,0:03:13.64,0:03:17.67,DCMain,KOGORO,0000,0000,0000,,What do you mean, you lost \Na year's worth of memories?
Dialogue: 0,0:03:20.36,0:03:22.72,DCMain,ESAKA,0000,0000,0000,,It happened one evening last week.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:23.54,0:03:27.34,DCMain,ESAKA,0000,0000,0000,,Before I knew it, I'd lost \Nconsciousness at the station.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:27.97,0:03:32.39,DCMain,ESAKA,0000,0000,0000,,Apparently I slipped down \Nthe stairs and hit my head.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:33.63,0:03:36.11,DCMain,ESAKA,0000,0000,0000,,When I returned to my workplace...
Dialogue: 0,0:03:38.69,0:03:41.86,DCItalic,BOSS A,0000,0000,0000,,Esaka, what have you been doing until now?
Dialogue: 0,0:03:42.17,0:03:45.92,DCItalic,BOSS A,0000,0000,0000,,You disappeared for a whole \Nyear after going out on a job.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:46.69,0:03:48.09,DCItalic,ESAKA,0000,0000,0000,,A year?
Dialogue: 0,0:03:50.56,0:03:52.62,DCMain,ESAKA,0000,0000,0000,,That was when I first learned about it.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:53.41,0:03:58.79,DCMain,ESAKA,0000,0000,0000,,I thought I'd left that morning \Nand returned that evening,
Dialogue: 0,0:03:58.79,0:04:01.63,DCMain,ESAKA,0000,0000,0000,,but an entire year had actually passed.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:06.49,0:04:12.44,DCMain,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,Something must've made him suffer \Nmemory loss while he was out on a job.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:12.44,0:04:18.15,DCMain,KOGORO,0000,0000,0000,,And one year later, something \Ncured him of his amnesia.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:18.58,0:04:20.78,DCMain,ESAKA,0000,0000,0000,,But it was too late.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:20.78,0:04:23.58,DCMain,ESAKA,0000,0000,0000,,I was fired a long time ago,
Dialogue: 0,0:04:23.58,0:04:27.00,DCMain,ESAKA,0000,0000,0000,,and when I returned to my apartment, \Nsomeone else was living there.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:29.37,0:04:32.41,DCMain,KOGORO,0000,0000,0000,,Like a sad Urashima Taro.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:32.70,0:04:39.17,DCMain,ESAKA,0000,0000,0000,,But I can't recall where I was or \Nwhat I was doing for a whole year.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:39.17,0:04:45.29,DCMain,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,So you regained your previous memories and \Nlost your memory of the past year instead.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:45.29,0:04:50.13,DCMain,KOGORO,0000,0000,0000,,Just like in that old movie "{\i1}Random Harvest{\i0}".
Dialogue: 0,0:04:50.13,0:04:54.44,DCMain,ESAKA,0000,0000,0000,,After thinking about it for a week, \NI thought these might lead somewhere.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:54.81,0:04:56.94,DCMain,ESAKA,0000,0000,0000,,I examined their usage history.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:56.94,0:05:04.95,DCMain,SIGN,0000,0000,0000,,{\an7\fs20\c&H252A2C&\3c&HE7E9EB&\shad0\b1}Usage History (20 Most Recent Results)\N\N{\fs18}Date / Type / Location / Type / Location
Dialogue: 0,0:04:56.94,0:05:04.95,DCMain,SIGN,0000,0000,0000,,{\an7\fs16\c&H252A2C&\3c&HE7E9EB&\shad0\b1\bord5}\N11/17 / Entry / Koneru / Exit / Shibahama\N11/17 / Entry / Shibahama / Exit / Koneru\N11/18 / Entry / Koneru / Exit / Midoridai\N11/18 / Entry / Midoridai / Exit / Koneru\N11/19 / Entry / Koneru / Exit / Murakucho\N11/19 / Entry / Murakucho / Exit / Koneru\N11/20 / Entry / Koneru / Exit / Murakucho\N11/20 / Entry / Murakucho / Exit / Koneru\N11/21 / Entry / Koneru / Exit / Komaire\N11/21 / Entry / Komaire / Exit / Koneru\N11/23 / Entry / Koneru / Exit / Butsuden
Dialogue: 0,0:04:57.59,0:05:04.63,DCMain,ESAKA,0000,0000,0000,,I went all over the place every day, but I \Nalways left from and returned to Koneru Station.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:05.29,0:05:07.57,DCMain,KOGORO,0000,0000,0000,,Maybe you lived in Koneru City.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:07.86,0:05:12.91,DCMain,ESAKA,0000,0000,0000,,I thought so, too, so I was walking around \Nin the hope that I would remember something.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:12.91,0:05:13.95,DCMain,ESAKA,0000,0000,0000,,That's when it happened.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:20.57,0:05:25.44,DCMain,ESAKA,0000,0000,0000,,Maybe I did something to \Nincur someone's enmity.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:26.24,0:05:30.72,DCMain,ESAKA,0000,0000,0000,,But I still want to know how I lived.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:30.98,0:05:34.04,DCMain,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,It is eerie not to know.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:34.04,0:05:37.60,DCMain,KOGORO,0000,0000,0000,,Koneru City, right? Let's \Ntalk another look around.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:38.13,0:05:39.36,DCMain,ESAKA,0000,0000,0000,,Mori-san...
Dialogue: 0,0:05:39.66,0:05:46.49,DCMain,KOGORO,0000,0000,0000,,I, Mori Kogoro, shall find the year \Nthat vanished from your memories.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:49.87,0:05:53.87,DCMain,SIGN,0000,0000,0000,,{\an7\b1\fnArial\fs20\shad0\pos(91,51)\c&HF7EAF7&\3c&H483542&}Discovered in the Mountains!
Dialogue: 0,0:05:49.87,0:05:53.87,DCMain,SIGN,0000,0000,0000,,{\an7\b1\fnArial\fs20\shad0\c&HF7EAF7&\3c&H483542&\pos(113,142)}Partially Skeletonized?!
Dialogue: 0,0:05:49.87,0:05:53.87,DCMain,SIGN,0000,0000,0000,,{\an8\fnTimesNewRoman\pos(230,230)\shad0\c&H68332B&\3c&HFFF0F5&\bord1.5}Kisugi Akira-san (38)
Dialogue: 0,0:05:49.87,0:05:53.87,DCMain,SIGN,0000,0000,0000,,{\an9\bord2\fnTimesNewRoman\fs22\shad0\c&HFDDFE5&\3c&H553539&\pos(535,253)}Frequent Con Artist?
Dialogue: 0,0:05:50.41,0:05:53.87,DCMain,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,One year is exactly twice as \Nlong as this person was missing for.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:54.13,0:05:58.12,DCMain,ESAKA,0000,0000,0000,,Oh, right. This guy \Nsuddenly disappeared, too.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:58.43,0:06:04.13,DCMain,KOGORO,0000,0000,0000,,He was found dead in the mountains \Nof Wakabadai three days ago.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:04.64,0:06:08.74,DCMain,KOGORO,0000,0000,0000,,{\an8}He was partially skeletonized, \Nbut he'd clearly been murdered.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:05.10,0:06:09.51,Location Signs,SIGN,0000,0000,0000,,{\fad(1148,809)\blur1}Outside the Metropolitan Area, Wakabadai
Dialogue: 0,0:06:08.74,0:06:15.39,DCMain,KOGORO,0000,0000,0000,,{\an8}It didn't take long to identify him as \NKisugi Akira, who'd been missing for six months.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:15.39,0:06:19.71,DCMain,KOGORO,0000,0000,0000,,Apparently they're having trouble finding \Nthe culprit who killed and buried him.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:19.71,0:06:24.19,DCMain,KOGORO,0000,0000,0000,,He was a con artist, and a lot of \Npeople had grudges against him.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:24.78,0:06:26.78,DCMain,ESAKA,0000,0000,0000,,Sounds like he was a bad person.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:27.06,0:06:30.28,DCMain,KOGORO,0000,0000,0000,,Well, not that he matters.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:32.41,0:06:36.29,DCMain,SIGN,0000,0000,0000,,{\an8\b1\fnArial\fs26\shad0\c&H4F5350&\3c&HD8E0DA&\fad(440,1)}Koneru Station
Dialogue: 0,0:06:42.65,0:06:46.17,DCMain,ESAKA,0000,0000,0000,,I can't remember anything, \Nno matter what I look at.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:46.41,0:06:53.05,DCMain,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,But if we find someone who knows you, we \Ncan ask them about your blank year, right?
Dialogue: 0,0:06:53.52,0:06:55.04,DCMain,KOGORO,0000,0000,0000,,That's true.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:55.04,0:06:58.81,DCMain,KOGORO,0000,0000,0000,,If you showed up in this \Nneighborhood with memory loss,
Dialogue: 0,0:06:59.14,0:07:02.56,DCMain,KOGORO,0000,0000,0000,,then maybe you visited that police box.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:06.86,0:07:08.79,DCMain,KOGORO,0000,0000,0000,,Is that your police box?
Dialogue: 0,0:07:10.95,0:07:12.95,DCMain,POLICE A,0000,0000,0000,,Yes. What about it?
Dialogue: 0,0:07:13.35,0:07:18.11,DCMain,KOGORO,0000,0000,0000,,I believe this man visited \Nyou about a year ago.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:22.16,0:07:24.15,DCMain,POLICE A,0000,0000,0000,,I don't recognize him.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:24.15,0:07:26.96,DCMain,POLICE A,0000,0000,0000,,I'm sorry, but I'm in a hurry.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:29.88,0:07:32.22,DCMain,KOGORO,0000,0000,0000,,We'll have to search on foot then.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:33.20,0:07:36.89,DCMain,KOGORO,0000,0000,0000,,Even though we split up and asked \Naround, we came up empty-handed.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:37.45,0:07:43.73,DCMain,KOGORO,0000,0000,0000,,There is a way to figure out what happened during \Nyour blank year besides finding someone who knows.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:45.01,0:07:46.52,DCMain,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,How?
Dialogue: 0,0:07:54.56,0:07:56.29,DCMain,ESAKA,0000,0000,0000,,What was that for?
Dialogue: 0,0:07:56.29,0:08:00.16,DCMain,KOGORO,0000,0000,0000,,It's shock treatment. \NYou remember now, right?
Dialogue: 0,0:08:03.80,0:08:06.66,DCMain,KOGORO,0000,0000,0000,,We could try slapping you really hard, too.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:08.40,0:08:10.80,DCItalic,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,He seems like he'd actually do it.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:11.88,0:08:15.91,DCMain,ESAKA,0000,0000,0000,,I know I'm the one who asked for \Nyour help, but you've done enough.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:15.91,0:08:17.68,DCMain,ESAKA,0000,0000,0000,,Let's go, Mori-san.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:20.47,0:08:21.84,DCMain,KOGORO,0000,0000,0000,,You're giving up?
Dialogue: 0,0:08:22.82,0:08:25.16,DCMain,ESAKA,0000,0000,0000,,I'm afraid to know after all.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:25.94,0:08:31.28,DCMain,ESAKA,0000,0000,0000,,If someone tried to kill me, I \Nmust've done something really awful.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:31.28,0:08:34.78,DCMain,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,Maybe it's just a misunderstanding.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:35.25,0:08:38.78,DCMain,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,It's hard to believe he's \Nsomeone who'd make enemies.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:39.11,0:08:43.16,DCMain,KOGORO,0000,0000,0000,,That's why we need to find \Nyour past, Esaka-kun.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:43.50,0:08:48.44,DCMain,KOGORO,0000,0000,0000,,If someone has a grudge against you because \Nof a misunderstanding, you need to clear it up.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:50.08,0:08:52.92,DCMain,ESAKA,0000,0000,0000,,Maybe it's not a \Nmisunderstanding! I'm scared!
Dialogue: 0,0:08:53.79,0:08:55.15,DCMain,KOGORO,0000,0000,0000,,Esaka-kun!
Dialogue: 0,0:08:53.79,0:08:55.15,DCMain,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,Esaka-san!
Dialogue: 0,0:09:10.37,0:09:12.86,DCMain,KOGORO,0000,0000,0000,,It's that patrol officer from earlier.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:12.86,0:09:16.74,DCMain,SIGN,0000,0000,0000,,{\an8\fnTimesNewRoman\bord2\shad0\fs22\c&H477072&\3c&HD1E7ED&\b1}Koneru Station Police Box
Dialogue: 0,0:09:15.23,0:09:16.74,DCMain,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,Mister, look.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:16.74,0:09:19.49,DCMain,SIGN,0000,0000,0000,,{\an8\b1\fnTimesNewRoman\shad0\pos(402,26)\c&H201A17&\3c&HF7FBFC&\bord2}Serial Burglar
Dialogue: 0,0:09:16.74,0:09:19.49,DCMain,SIGN,0000,0000,0000,,{\an8\b1\fnTimesNewRoman\shad0\c&H45D0DF&\3c&H000000&\bord2\pos(297,100)}W\Na\Nn\Nt\Ne\Nd
Dialogue: 0,0:09:16.74,0:09:19.49,DCMain,SIGN,0000,0000,0000,,{\an8\b1\fnTimesNewRoman\shad0\c&H716B5E&\3c&HF5F3E5&\bord1.5\fs15.5\pos(399,280)}Suspect Kuroda Keinobu (42)
Dialogue: 0,0:09:18.08,0:09:19.49,DCMain,BOTH,0000,0000,0000,,A burglar?
Dialogue: 0,0:09:19.76,0:09:23.25,DCMain,KOGORO,0000,0000,0000,,How brazen of him to disguise \Nhimself as a police officer.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:23.52,0:09:26.37,DCMain,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,There was no point in asking him \Nsince he was a fake officer.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:26.68,0:09:28.73,DCMain,KOGORO,0000,0000,0000,,You're right. All right, let's go.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:29.50,0:09:31.59,DCMain,ESAKA,0000,0000,0000,,I-I said forget it!
Dialogue: 0,0:09:31.59,0:09:32.55,DCMain,KOGORO,0000,0000,0000,,No!
Dialogue: 0,0:09:41.24,0:09:43.27,DCMain,POLICE B,0000,0000,0000,,Yeah, I remember him.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:44.39,0:09:47.14,DCMain,KOGORO,0000,0000,0000,,He visited you a year ago?
Dialogue: 0,0:09:47.37,0:09:51.45,DCMain,POLICE B,0000,0000,0000,,Apparently he was bewildered \Nand suffering from memory loss
Dialogue: 0,0:09:51.45,0:09:54.15,DCMain,POLICE B,0000,0000,0000,,according to the person who brought him here.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:54.66,0:09:58.08,DCMain,POLICE B,0000,0000,0000,,Maybe he was robbed,
Dialogue: 0,0:09:58.08,0:10:00.06,DCMain,POLICE B,0000,0000,0000,,but he didn't have any identification \Non him or even a phone.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:00.06,0:10:03.16,DCMain,POLICE B,0000,0000,0000,,I checked the missing persons reports, too.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:03.38,0:10:05.22,DCMain,KOGORO,0000,0000,0000,,But you didn't find him.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:05.22,0:10:09.17,DCMain,KOGORO,0000,0000,0000,,After all, more than 80,000 \Npeople go missing a year.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:09.43,0:10:12.67,DCMain,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,What happened to Esaka-san after that?
Dialogue: 0,0:10:13.18,0:10:18.63,DCMain,POLICE B,0000,0000,0000,,The person who brought him here, Kinbara \NTakuzo-san, said he'd take care of him.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:20.77,0:10:24.46,DCMain,KOGORO,0000,0000,0000,,If we can find that person, we'll know \Nwhat happened during your blank year.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:24.46,0:10:28.43,DCMain,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,And probably whoever holds a grudge \Nagainst you over a misunderstanding.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:29.69,0:10:31.61,DCMain,ESAKA,0000,0000,0000,,I'm afraid of a possible misunderstanding,
Dialogue: 0,0:10:32.22,0:10:37.01,DCMain,ESAKA,0000,0000,0000,,but if Kinbara-san took care of \Nme, then I need to thank him.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:39.38,0:10:40.45,DCMain,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,This is the place.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:42.45,0:10:44.95,DCMain,SIGN,0000,0000,0000,,{\an8\fnTimesNewRoman\shad0\c&H2B2D28&\3c&H8D9694&\b1}Kinbara Takuzo & Tae
Dialogue: 0,0:10:44.33,0:10:44.95,DCItalic,TAE,0000,0000,0000,,Yes?
Dialogue: 0,0:10:45.25,0:10:48.06,DCMain,KOGORO,0000,0000,0000,,I'm Mori, a detective.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:48.06,0:10:51.46,DCItalic,TAE,0000,0000,0000,,I see. One moment, please.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:55.04,0:10:56.09,DCMain,KINBARA,0000,0000,0000,,Taro-kun?
Dialogue: 0,0:10:57.60,0:11:00.72,DCMain,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,Looks like this guy is Kinbara-san.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:00.92,0:11:03.88,DCMain,KOGORO,0000,0000,0000,,But didn't he just call him Taro-kun?
Dialogue: 0,0:11:06.09,0:11:07.72,DCMain,TAE,0000,0000,0000,,Thank you for waiting.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:08.99,0:11:10.23,DCMain,TAE,0000,0000,0000,,Taro-kun?
Dialogue: 0,0:11:10.42,0:11:13.21,DCMain,TAE,0000,0000,0000,,Where have you been this past week?
Dialogue: 0,0:11:13.21,0:11:17.23,DCMain,ESAKA,0000,0000,0000,,Taro? My name is Esaka Ritsuo.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:19.08,0:11:20.42,DCMain,TAE,0000,0000,0000,,Could it be?
Dialogue: 0,0:11:21.20,0:11:23.24,DCMain,KINBARA,0000,0000,0000,,Your amnesia's been cured?
Dialogue: 0,0:11:24.79,0:11:30.62,DCMain,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,Since not having a name for you was inconvenient, \Nthey must've temporarily named you Taro-san.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:30.97,0:11:33.66,DCMain,KINBARA,0000,0000,0000,,Yeah, Koneru Taro-kun.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:34.71,0:11:36.25,DCMain,TAE,0000,0000,0000,,That's right.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:39.73,0:11:43.89,DCMain,ESAKA,0000,0000,0000,,I'm sorry, but I have no memory at all
Dialogue: 0,0:11:44.48,0:11:48.14,DCMain,ESAKA,0000,0000,0000,,of being called that or \Nyou taking care of me.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:49.16,0:11:50.15,DCMain,KINBARA,0000,0000,0000,,What?
Dialogue: 0,0:11:54.56,0:11:58.02,Character Names,SIGN,0000,0000,0000,,{\fad(445,387)\pos(328,297)\3c&H913738&}Kinbara Takuzo (71)\NBicycle Parking Lot Employee
Dialogue: 0,0:11:55.30,0:11:58.40,DCMain,KINBARA,0000,0000,0000,,{\an8}I see. I understand.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:58.57,0:12:01.99,Character Names,SIGN,0000,0000,0000,,{\fad(439,395)\pos(306,296)\3c&H964A64&}Kinbara Tae (70)\NTakuzo's Wife
Dialogue: 0,0:11:58.94,0:12:02.90,DCMain,TAE,0000,0000,0000,,{\an8}Your amnesia's been cured, and instead...
Dialogue: 0,0:12:03.14,0:12:06.09,DCMain,KANEHARA,0000,0000,0000,,You lost your memories of the past year.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:06.09,0:12:11.91,DCMain,KOGORO,0000,0000,0000,,We came because we wanted to know \Nhow Esaka-kun spent that year.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:12.17,0:12:17.19,DCMain,KANEHARA,0000,0000,0000,,So that's how it is. In that case, \Nlet's invite them over, too.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:18.04,0:12:20.60,DCMain,TAE,0000,0000,0000,,I'm sure they'll come running.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:30.23,0:12:32.21,DCMain,ESAKA,0000,0000,0000,,A-Are they angry?
Dialogue: 0,0:12:32.21,0:12:33.79,DCMain,ESAKA,0000,0000,0000,,Then there's no mistaking it.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:33.79,0:12:38.69,DCMain,ESAKA,0000,0000,0000,,I must've done something \Nto incur their enmity!
Dialogue: 0,0:12:41.32,0:12:46.45,DCItalic,KOGORO,0000,0000,0000,,Does everyone here have a \Ngrudge against Esaka-kun?
Dialogue: 0,0:12:57.60,0:13:00.08,DCMain,HIDA,0000,0000,0000,,How dare you suddenly vanish like that.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:00.08,0:13:02.88,DCMain,HIDA,0000,0000,0000,,We've been worried about you this past week.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:03.66,0:13:04.63,DCMain,ESAKA,0000,0000,0000,,Worried?
Dialogue: 0,0:13:06.26,0:13:09.26,DCMain,TOKO,0000,0000,0000,,But I'm glad you're all right.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:09.57,0:13:12.77,DCMain,MAMORU,0000,0000,0000,,And that you remembered who \Nyou are and where you're from.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:13.22,0:13:17.40,DCMain,HIDA,0000,0000,0000,,It's a little sad that you \Ndon't remember us, though.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:19.21,0:13:20.40,DCMain,ESAKA,0000,0000,0000,,I'm sorry.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:23.06,0:13:27.82,DCMain,KINBARA,0000,0000,0000,,{\an8}Let me reintroduce you. This is Hida \NKeisuke-kun, the construction company president.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:26.20,0:13:29.41,Character Names,SIGN,0000,0000,0000,,{\fad(439,1)\pos(299,296)\3c&HAB6E65&}Hida Keisuke (53)\NConstruction Company Manager
Dialogue: 0,0:13:27.82,0:13:29.41,DCMain,HIDA,0000,0000,0000,,{\an8}Welcome back, Taro-kun.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:29.41,0:13:33.02,DCMain,KINBARA,0000,0000,0000,,{\an8}Mizutani Toko-san from \Nthe Koneru Credit Union.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:31.95,0:13:35.41,Character Names,SIGN,0000,0000,0000,,{\fad(444,1)\pos(357,296)\3c&H9A416C&}Mizutani Toko (26)\NBank Employee
Dialogue: 0,0:13:33.02,0:13:35.41,DCMain,TOKO,0000,0000,0000,,{\an8}I'm glad to be able to talk to you again.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:35.61,0:13:38.17,DCMain,KANEHARA,0000,0000,0000,,{\an8}Cram school student Chimura Mamoru-kun.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:37.25,0:13:40.67,Character Names,SIGN,0000,0000,0000,,{\fad(400,1)\pos(235,298)\3c&H9A4258&}Chimura Mamoru (20)\NCram School Student
Dialogue: 0,0:13:38.17,0:13:40.67,DCMain,MAMORU,0000,0000,0000,,{\an8}It's kind of embarrassing \Nto be formally reintroduced.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:41.00,0:13:45.02,DCMain,KINBARA,0000,0000,0000,,These three from the neighborhood took \Npity on you and your memory loss,
Dialogue: 0,0:13:45.02,0:13:47.43,DCMain,KINBARA,0000,0000,0000,,so they helped out here and there.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:47.43,0:13:50.18,DCMain,TAE,0000,0000,0000,,They kept encouraging and supporting you.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:50.47,0:13:52.68,DCMain,HIDA,0000,0000,0000,,You did more than any of us, Kinbara-san.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:52.68,0:13:56.15,DCMain,HIDA,0000,0000,0000,,You looked after him since you consider \Nyourself the steward of the neighborhood.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:56.15,0:13:59.19,DCMain,MAMORU,0000,0000,0000,,All I did was ask my dad for a little favor.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:59.42,0:14:03.60,DCMain,KINBARA,0000,0000,0000,,Mamoru-kun's father let you \Nlive in an apartment he owns,
Dialogue: 0,0:14:03.60,0:14:06.44,DCMain,KINBARA,0000,0000,0000,,and you worked at Hida-kun's \Nconstruction company.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:06.70,0:14:09.32,DCMain,HIDA,0000,0000,0000,,At construction sites all around the city.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:11.83,0:14:14.20,DCMain,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,So that's why you went all \Nkinds of places every day.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:14.53,0:14:18.96,DCMain,TAE,0000,0000,0000,,Toko-san frequently brought \Nyou meals when she cooked.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:20.04,0:14:23.96,DCMain,TOKO,0000,0000,0000,,It's embarrassing. I'm not much of a cook.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:25.92,0:14:30.63,DCMain,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,So Esaka-san owes these \Npeople a great deal, too.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:31.49,0:14:34.14,DCMain,KOGORO,0000,0000,0000,,Sounds like you were living with support
Dialogue: 0,0:14:34.14,0:14:38.73,DCMain,KOGORO,0000,0000,0000,,from the goodwill of the kind-hearted \NKinbaras and these three.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:39.66,0:14:40.56,DCMain,ESAKA,0000,0000,0000,,Yeah.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:49.27,0:14:53.46,DCMain,ESAKA,0000,0000,0000,,Thank you for the past year.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:57.90,0:15:01.63,DCMain,TOKO,0000,0000,0000,,I'm so glad you're doing well.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:02.14,0:15:05.11,DCMain,ESAKA,0000,0000,0000,,I don't know how to thank you.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:05.93,0:15:08.58,DCMain,KOGORO,0000,0000,0000,,We've learned how you spent the past year,
Dialogue: 0,0:15:08.58,0:15:12.01,DCMain,KOGORO,0000,0000,0000,,but one question remains.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:12.48,0:15:18.27,DCMain,KOGORO,0000,0000,0000,,This afternoon, Esaka-kun was nearly \Nkilled by someone here in Koneru City.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:21.02,0:15:25.40,DCMain,ESAKA,0000,0000,0000,,Did anyone have a grudge against me?
Dialogue: 0,0:15:27.68,0:15:29.28,DCMain,HIDA,0000,0000,0000,,Of course not.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:29.45,0:15:33.03,DCMain,KINBARA,0000,0000,0000,,People loved you. You did nothing \Nto make people hate you.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:33.27,0:15:36.37,DCMain,TOKO,0000,0000,0000,,That's right. You're \Noverthinking it, Taro-san.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:37.65,0:15:40.41,DCMain,KOGORO,0000,0000,0000,,Then it really must be a misunderstanding.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:40.72,0:15:42.70,DCMain,HIDA,0000,0000,0000,,That's inconceivable, too.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:42.70,0:15:45.65,DCMain,HIDA,0000,0000,0000,,You're probably imagining that \Nsomeone tried to kill you.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:45.65,0:15:47.07,DCMain,KINBARA,0000,0000,0000,,I can only assume that's the case.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:47.42,0:15:48.82,DCMain,KOGORO,0000,0000,0000,,But...
Dialogue: 0,0:15:48.82,0:15:52.15,DCMain,ESAKA,0000,0000,0000,,Maybe it was just my imagination.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:52.43,0:15:57.93,DCMain,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,If the people close to you say so, then \Nmaybe nobody has a grudge against you.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:58.36,0:16:00.49,DCMain,KOGORO,0000,0000,0000,,Maybe you weren't pushed.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:00.49,0:16:04.09,DCMain,KOGORO,0000,0000,0000,,Maybe someone just happened to bump into you.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:06.69,0:16:10.11,DCMain,HIDA,0000,0000,0000,,That's right! More importantly, \Nwe need to celebrate.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:10.42,0:16:12.61,DCMain,TOKO,0000,0000,0000,,After all, you're doing well.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:12.94,0:16:15.12,DCMain,MAMORU,0000,0000,0000,,And you've recovered from your amnesia.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:18.03,0:16:19.54,DCMain,KINBARA,0000,0000,0000,,Do you drink?
Dialogue: 0,0:16:19.70,0:16:22.41,DCMain,KOGORO,0000,0000,0000,,I enjoy a bit now and then.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:23.05,0:16:26.12,DCItalic,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,Oh, you enjoy it endlessly.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:31.16,0:16:34.68,DCMain,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,We don't have to wait for Kinbara-san's wife?
Dialogue: 0,0:16:35.05,0:16:39.98,DCMain,TOKO,0000,0000,0000,,Tae-san's frail. She's \Nalways in and out of bed.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:39.98,0:16:44.69,DCMain,ESAKA,0000,0000,0000,,I made someone like that \Nworry this past week?
Dialogue: 0,0:16:45.06,0:16:47.69,DCMain,ESAKA,0000,0000,0000,,If only I'd visited sooner.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:47.96,0:16:51.41,DCMain,KOGORO,0000,0000,0000,,Aren't you glad you didn't run away earlier?
Dialogue: 0,0:16:51.41,0:16:53.19,DCMain,HIDA,0000,0000,0000,,You tried to run?
Dialogue: 0,0:16:53.41,0:16:55.11,DCMain,ESAKA,0000,0000,0000,,Mori-san!
Dialogue: 0,0:16:59.33,0:17:02.87,DCMain,AMANO,0000,0000,0000,,No, Shi-chan! No!
Dialogue: 0,0:17:02.87,0:17:04.62,DCMain,AMANO,0000,0000,0000,,I'm sorry.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:05.09,0:17:06.00,DCMain,AMANO,0000,0000,0000,,Come on.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:08.13,0:17:10.55,DCMain,ESAKA,0000,0000,0000,,I don't like dogs.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:11.11,0:17:14.38,DCMain,ESAKA,0000,0000,0000,,Especially not barking \Ndogs like Shishimaru.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:16.85,0:17:20.41,DCMain,ESAKA,0000,0000,0000,,A stray bit me on the butt \Nwhen I was in kindergarten.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:20.41,0:17:22.77,DCMain,ESAKA,0000,0000,0000,,Since then, I've been afraid of dogs.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:23.75,0:17:25.02,DCMain,KANEHARA,0000,0000,0000,,Shishimaru?
Dialogue: 0,0:17:25.02,0:17:28.40,DCMain,KANEHARA,0000,0000,0000,,You remembered Amano-san's dog Shishimaru?
Dialogue: 0,0:17:33.47,0:17:37.66,DCMain,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,You may not like dogs, but one \Nhelped you remember something.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:37.93,0:17:41.16,DCMain,KOGORO,0000,0000,0000,,See? Shock therapy is effective.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:42.06,0:17:45.53,DCMain,ESAKA,0000,0000,0000,,The memories that had been completely \Nclosed off to me are returning.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:46.41,0:17:49.42,DCMain,SIGN,0000,0000,0000,,{\an8\fnTimesNewRoman\fs30\shad0\c&HA79EA4&\3c&H57524B&}Yakitori Izakaya
Dialogue: 0,0:18:01.31,0:18:02.53,DCMain,ESAKA,0000,0000,0000,,It's no use.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:02.53,0:18:06.94,DCMain,ESAKA,0000,0000,0000,,I thought I'd be able to remember something \Nbesides the dog's name, but I can't.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:07.25,0:18:11.69,DCMain,KANEHARA,0000,0000,0000,,It's all right. You don't \Nhave to try so hard. Right?
Dialogue: 0,0:18:12.08,0:18:13.44,DCMain,ALL,0000,0000,0000,,Yeah.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:17.96,0:18:21.57,DCMain,HIDA,0000,0000,0000,,We called your phone a bunch \Nof times, but no one answered.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:22.42,0:18:26.08,DCMain,ESAKA,0000,0000,0000,,I think I lost it when I fell \Ndown the station stairs.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:26.08,0:18:30.16,DCMain,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,Mister, you lose your phone all \Nthe time when you get drunk.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:39.69,0:18:42.85,DCMain,MAMORU,0000,0000,0000,,It's rumbling out there. \NIt'll probably strike again.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:44.14,0:18:45.57,DCMain,ESAKA,0000,0000,0000,,Thunder...
Dialogue: 0,0:18:45.57,0:18:48.16,DCMain,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,You don't like thunder either?
Dialogue: 0,0:18:48.16,0:18:49.99,DCMain,ESAKA,0000,0000,0000,,It's not that.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:49.99,0:18:53.84,DCMain,ESAKA,0000,0000,0000,,I felt like I remembered a scene \Nof particular interest to me.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:54.43,0:18:58.77,DCMain,ESAKA,0000,0000,0000,,I wonder what it was. Thunder... dogs...
Dialogue: 0,0:18:58.77,0:19:00.99,DCMain,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,Dogs have something to do with it, too?
Dialogue: 0,0:19:00.99,0:19:03.86,DCMain,KOGORO,0000,0000,0000,,Then that's not a memory, it's a desire.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:04.51,0:19:09.75,DCMain,KOGORO,0000,0000,0000,,You wish dogs would be struck by \Nlightning and burnt to a crisp.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:11.05,0:19:16.13,DCMain,TOKO,0000,0000,0000,,How cruel, Mori-san. How could you wish \Nfor dogs to be struck by lightning?
Dialogue: 0,0:19:16.13,0:19:20.18,DCMain,KOGORO,0000,0000,0000,,Oh, no. I was just speaking for Esaka-kun.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:20.18,0:19:23.18,DCMain,ESAKA,0000,0000,0000,,Not even I'd wish for that.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:23.50,0:19:26.28,DCMain,KINBARA,0000,0000,0000,,I'm going to pop home for a minute.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:26.28,0:19:29.56,DCMain,KINBARA,0000,0000,0000,,I'm worried if she's remembered \Nto take her medicine.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:29.82,0:19:32.69,DCMain,HIDA,0000,0000,0000,,Kinbara-san really loves his wife.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:32.69,0:19:34.69,DCMain,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,I see.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:35.94,0:19:37.74,DCMain,MAMORU,0000,0000,0000,,It looks like rain.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:37.74,0:19:42.92,DCMain,KINBARA,0000,0000,0000,,There's that, too, so I thought I'd \Ngo get umbrellas for everyone.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:45.94,0:19:48.59,DCMain,ESAKA,0000,0000,0000,,He really is a nice person.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:48.59,0:19:51.87,DCMain,HIDA,0000,0000,0000,,That's why he took care of \Nyou when you were at a loss.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:52.89,0:19:56.88,DCMain,ESAKA,0000,0000,0000,,Not just Kinbara-san. All of you, too.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:59.61,0:20:01.38,DCMain,ESAKA,0000,0000,0000,,I wish I could remember.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:01.74,0:20:04.19,DCMain,KOGORO,0000,0000,0000,,You will eventually.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:04.19,0:20:06.14,DCMain,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,Something will make you remember.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:17.14,0:20:18.17,DCMain,ESAKA,0000,0000,0000,,They're right.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:19.49,0:20:22.06,DCMain,ESAKA,0000,0000,0000,,I'm sure something will make me remember.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:23.11,0:20:25.95,DCItalic,ANNOUNCER,0000,0000,0000,,{\an8}Three days ago, Kisugi \NAkira-san was found dead
Dialogue: 0,0:20:25.95,0:20:29.50,DCItalic,ANNOUNCER,0000,0000,0000,,{\an8}in the mountains near \NWakabadai outside the city.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:28.79,0:20:34.17,DCMain,SIGN,0000,0000,0000,,{\an9\fs20\bord2\shad0\pos(552,259)\c&H352D24&\3c&HDFE9E1&\b1}December
Dialogue: 0,0:20:29.50,0:20:33.38,DCItalic,ANNOUNCER,0000,0000,0000,,{\an8}According to those with \Nconnections at the investigation HQ,
Dialogue: 0,0:20:33.38,0:20:38.65,DCItalic,ANNOUNCER,0000,0000,0000,,{\an8}they've determined that he was killed and \Nburied six months earlier on June 10th.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:34.17,0:20:41.17,DCMain,SIGN,0000,0000,0000,,{\an2\b1\fnTimesNewRoman\shad0\c&HFBFBFB&\3c&H99372D&\fs21\pos(321,231)}Con Artist Murdered Six Months Ago
Dialogue: 0,0:20:38.65,0:20:41.17,DCItalic,ANNOUNCER,0000,0000,0000,,{\an8}Police are currently working \Non identifying the culprit.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:45.80,0:20:48.18,DCItalic,ESAKA,0000,0000,0000,,It didn't bother me until now,
Dialogue: 0,0:20:48.18,0:20:51.31,DCItalic,ESAKA,0000,0000,0000,,so why am I so interested in it?
Dialogue: 0,0:20:48.18,0:20:51.31,DCMain,SIGN TOP,0000,0000,0000,,{\an8\b1\fnArial\fs30\c&HA5A3A1&\3c&H050303&\shad1}Missing Man Found Dead
Dialogue: 0,0:20:48.18,0:20:51.31,DCMain,SIGN RIGHT,0000,0000,0000,,{\an9\pos(634,167)\fnArial\b1\shad0\c&H050303&\3c&HA5A3A1&\bord3\fs22}Body Found in Wakabadai \NMountains Identified
Dialogue: 0,0:20:48.18,0:20:51.31,DCMain,SIGN PHOTO,0000,0000,0000,,{\an1\fs18\shad0\frz1.109\pos(155,250)\c&H050303&\3c&HA5A3A1&\bord2.5}Kisugi Akira-san (38) Found Dead
Dialogue: 0,0:20:51.82,0:20:55.16,DCItalic,ESAKA,0000,0000,0000,,But I feel like they're connected somehow.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:55.16,0:20:58.00,DCItalic,ESAKA,0000,0000,0000,,Thunder... dogs...
Dialogue: 0,0:21:13.25,0:21:17.38,Location Signs,SIGN,0000,0000,0000,,{\fad(1898,814)\blur1\pos(318,292)}Two Days Later
Dialogue: 0,0:21:17.26,0:21:19.00,DCMain,KOGORO,0000,0000,0000,,It's been two days.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:19.00,0:21:21.80,DCMain,KOGORO,0000,0000,0000,,Maybe he's been able to remember something.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:21.80,0:21:26.20,DCMain,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,Should we try shock therapy \Nagain if he hasn't?
Dialogue: 0,0:21:26.62,0:21:29.36,DCMain,KOGORO,0000,0000,0000,,That's one way to do it.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:30.36,0:21:34.00,DCMain,KOGORO,0000,0000,0000,,Didn't he say it's up ahead?
Dialogue: 0,0:21:34.00,0:21:34.81,DCMain,KOGORO,0000,0000,0000,,Huh?
Dialogue: 0,0:21:35.92,0:21:36.81,DCMain,KOGORO,0000,0000,0000,,Inspector!
Dialogue: 0,0:21:37.45,0:21:38.44,DCMain,TAKAGI,0000,0000,0000,,Mori-san.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:38.81,0:21:41.00,DCMain,MEGURE,0000,0000,0000,,You again?
Dialogue: 0,0:21:41.75,0:21:43.61,DCMain,KOGORO,0000,0000,0000,,I know someone who lives at this apartment.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:43.93,0:21:45.49,DCMain,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,What happened?
Dialogue: 0,0:21:47.93,0:21:49.49,DCMain,KOGORO,0000,0000,0000,,C-Could it be?
Dialogue: 0,0:21:50.75,0:21:51.99,DCMain,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,Esaka-san?
Dialogue: 0,0:21:52.16,0:21:54.67,DCMain,TAKAGI,0000,0000,0000,,Then your acquaintance must be...
Dialogue: 0,0:21:54.67,0:21:59.75,DCMain,MEGURE,0000,0000,0000,,The autopsy revealed that he died last \Nnight around 7PM after consuming a poison.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:00.00,0:22:02.80,DCMain,MEGURE,0000,0000,0000,,Judging by the circumstances, it \Nwas almost certainly a suicide.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:03.46,0:22:04.76,DCMain,KOGORO,0000,0000,0000,,Suicide?
Dialogue: 0,0:22:07.23,0:22:12.01,DCMain,MEGURE,0000,0000,0000,,Apparently he regretted \Nsome bad choices he made.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:12.92,0:22:14.52,DCMain,KOGORO,0000,0000,0000,,So he killed himself?
Dialogue: 0,0:22:17.61,0:22:21.94,DCItalic,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,Really? Was this really a suicide?
Dialogue: 0,0:23:44.94,0:24:08.96,DCEpPreview,SIGN,0000,0000,0000,,Episode Preview
Dialogue: 0,0:23:45.31,0:23:50.45,DCMain,MEGURE,0000,0000,0000,,What we believe is a suicide \Nnote was left on that computer.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:48.61,0:23:50.45,DCMain,SIGN,0000,0000,0000,,{\an8\fnArial\bord2\shad0\pos(321,132)\c&H543631&\3c&HF9F7F5&}Though it's been six months, I can't escape my guilt.\NThe only apology I can offer is death.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:50.77,0:23:53.53,DCMain,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,You said it was locked.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:53.53,0:23:56.11,DCMain,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,Was the door chain on the \Nfront door locked, too?
Dialogue: 0,0:23:56.11,0:23:59.62,DCMain,TAKAGI,0000,0000,0000,,No, the chain wasn't locked,
Dialogue: 0,0:23:59.62,0:24:02.17,DCMain,TAKAGI,0000,0000,0000,,but both keys were here.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:02.57,0:24:06.46,DCMain,TAKAGI,0000,0000,0000,,One in the back of the desk drawer, \Nand one in that jacket pocket.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:07.74,0:24:08.96,DCMain,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,Hey, listen.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:08.96,0:24:14.97,DCNextEp,SIGN,0000,0000,0000,,The Blank Year \N(Part Two)
Dialogue: 0,0:24:09.46,0:24:13.74,DCMain,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,The next episode of Conan is \N"The Blank Year, Part Two!"
Dialogue: 0,0:24:29.98,0:24:32.32,DCMain,KOGORO,0000,0000,0000,,Next Conan's hint, Kudo-kun!
Dialogue: 0,0:24:29.98,0:24:34.91,Hint,SIGN,0000,0000,0000,,Thunder and Lightning
Dialogue: 0,0:24:32.32,0:24:33.93,DCMain,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,Thunder and lightning!
Dialogue: 0,0:24:34.91,0:24:35.69,DCMain,KOGORO,0000,0000,0000,,{\an8}I can't remember.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:34.91,0:24:39.91,Don'tMiss,SIGN,0000,0000,0000,,Don't miss the next episode.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:35.69,0:24:36.38,DCMain,TAKAGI,0000,0000,0000,,{\an8}Can't remember what?
Dialogue: 0,0:24:36.38,0:24:37.87,DCMain,KOGORO,0000,0000,0000,,{\an8}What I was trying to remember.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:37.87,0:24:39.60,DCMain,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,{\an8}Relatable.
